CV Project Contribution Guidelines

Thank you for considering contributing to the CV project! 
We appreciate your interest in making this project better. 
To ensure a smooth and productive collaboration, please follow these guidelines when contributing.

Code of Conduct
Please review and adhere to our Code of Conduct to foster a welcoming and inclusive community.

How to Contribute?
  
1) Fork the repository to your GitHub account.
    Clone the forked repository to your local machine.
    Create a new branch for your changes: git checkout -b your-feature.
    Make your changes and commit them: git commit -m "Description of your changes".
    Push the changes to your forked repository: git push origin your-feature.
    Create a pull request from your branch to the main branch of this repository.
    Ensure the pull request includes a clear description of your changes and the reason behind them.
    Branching Strategy

2) The main branch represents the stable version of the project.
    Please submit your pull requests against the main branch.
    Use feature branches to work on your changes.
    Coding Standards
3) Follow the PEP 8 coding style guidelines.
    Ensure your code is well-documented and includes explanatory comments where necessary.
    Write meaningful variable and function names.
    Testing Guidelines
    Include relevant test cases with your changes.
    Ensure all tests pass before submitting the pull request.
    Documentation
4) Include documentation for new features or changes to existing functionality.
    Update the project's README or other relevant documentation as needed.

5) Issue Tracking
    If you find a bug or have a feature request, check the issue tracker first to avoid duplicate submissions.
      Use descriptive titles and provide detailed information in issue reports.
      Submitting Pull Requests
6) Provide a clear and descriptive pull request description.
    Make sure your code has been reviewed and meets our coding standards.
    Review Process
    Pull requests will be reviewed by project maintainers.
    Feedback will be provided, and changes may be requested before merging.
    Acknowledgments
  
We are grateful for your contributions! 
  Your efforts help improve the CV project and benefit the community.
  We will acknowledge your contributions in the project's documentation.

License
By contributing to this project, you agree that your contributions will be licensed under the LICENSE of this project.
If you have any questions or need further assistance, feel free to reach out to us through "kompasj@mail.ru".

Happy contributing!
